  "definitions": [
    {
      "definition": "A malignant B-cell lymphoproliferative process affecting the blood, bone marrow, and spleen.  The B-prolymphocytes are medium-sized, round lymphoid cells with prominent nucleoli.  The B-prolymphocytes must exceed 55% of lymphoid cells in the blood.  Cases of transformed chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) and CLL with increased prolymphocytes are excluded.  The prognosis is poor.  (WHO, 2001)",
      "type": "DEFINITION",
      "source": "NCI"
    }
  ],
